urls.title: The Doge Crown
urls.description: Personally designed by Domenico Dolce and Stefano Gabbana, The Doge Crown is inspired by Venice’s most famous location: Piazza San Marco. Within Piazza San Marco resides the Doge’s Palace (also known as Palazzo Ducale) along with the famous clock tower. On the top of the clock tower there is the symbol of Venice, the sun with a face, which is also represented inside the clock tower. This museum-grade piece of sculptural art took hundreds of hours to create by hand across both the physical and digital versions. Legend has it that the special collector that owns The Doge Crown will thereafter be the anointed King of Crypto...
